debut for [[MKE Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc|Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc]] on 18 February 2012.{{Citation needed|date=April 2014}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=526&kisiId=950263 Player profile] at TFF.org\n* [https://int.soccerway.com/players/sinan-kurumu/230354/ Sinan Kurumu\u015f] at Soccerway\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kurumus, Sinan}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from \u0130neg\u00f6l]]\n[[Category:Turkish footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkey youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:MKE Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc footballers]]\n[[Category:Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:Boluspor footballers]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Turkey-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Geschichte", "label": "safe", "comment": "lk", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinan_Kurumu%C5%9F"}
{"title_page": "Eric Wahlforss", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| pre-nominals       = \n| name               = Eric Alfred Wahlforss\n| post-nominals      = \n| image              =  <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| image_upright      = \n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|df=y|1895|5|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Helsinki]], [[Grand Duchy of Finland]]\n| death_date         = {{Death date and age|df=y|1951|10|5|1895|5|21}}<ref name=\"Kko: V\">{{cite book |last1=Laati |first1=Iisakki |last2=Havu |first2=Ilmari |last3=Blomstedt |first3=Yrj\u00f6 |author-link3= Yrj\u00f6 Blomstedt |last4=Poij\u00e4rvi |first4= L. Arvi P. |year=1961 |orig-year= |chapter=V |chapter-url=https://fi.wikisource.org/wiki/Kuka_kukin_oli:_V |title=Kuka kukin oli |script-title= |trans-title=Who Was Who in Finland |language=Finnish |location=Helsinki |publisher=Otava }}</ref>\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = suicide<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\">Zilliacus: ''Ukkohauki.'' pp. 168\u2013181.</ref>\n| body_discovered    = \n| resting_place      = \n| burial_place       =  <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| education          = [[DSc]], [[chemistry]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      =  ''Nya monosubstitutionsprodukter av reten'' (doctoral thesis, 1924)<ref name=\"Kko: V\"/><ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n| home_town          = \n| title              =  <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office= may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as \"Office\" (e.g. public office or appointments) -->\n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| spouse             = Christiane Wahlforss<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = [[Alfred Wahlforss|Henrik Alfred Wahlforss]] and<br/>Emilia Elisabeth L\u00e5nghjelm\n| relatives          = [[Wilhelm Wahlforss]] (brother)<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.24-43\">Zilliacus: ''Svartista Oulunkyl\u00e4\u00e4n.'' pp. 24\u201343.</ref>\n| family             = \n| awards             = \n| module             = {{Infobox officeholder | embed = yes\n | office             = Director of [[W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]] Selluloosa Oy [[\u00c4\u00e4nekoski]] [[Pulp Mill]]\n | term_start         = 1942\n | term_end           = 1951<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n | predecessor        = \n | successor          = \n}}\n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n}}\n\n'''Eric Alfred Wahlforss''' (21 May 1895 \u2013 5 October 1951) was a Finnish [[chemist]] and businessman.\n\nWahlforss's father died when he was young. He studied [[chemistry]] and did his [[DSc]] in 1924. He emigrated to United States and worked as a chemist for [[Arthur D. Little]], Industrial Process Ltd, [[Hammermill Paper Company|Hammermill]] and [[Glidden (paints)|Glidden Co]]. He returned to Finland and in 1937\u20131941 he worked for [[A. Ahlstr\u00f6m]]. In 1941 Wahlforss got a manager position in [[W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]] Selluloosa Oy [[\u00c4\u00e4nekoski]] Pulp Mill, where he stayed until his death 1951.\n\n== Early years and studies ==\nWahlforss was born as fourth and youngest child of chemist [[Alfred Wahlforss]] and Emilia Elisabeth n\u00e9e L\u00e5nghjelm. His older brother was [[Wilhelm Wahlforss]], who later became a notable company manager. The father got [[Paralysis|paralysed]] in 1896, when Eric was just one year old, and died in 1899.<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.24-43\"/> Wahlforss did his [[Matriculation exam (Finland)|matriculation exam]] in 1914 and graduated MSc in 1919. In the following year he did a field trip to [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] and graduated [[Candidate of Philosophy]]. In 1924 he graduated [[DSc]]. The topic of his thesis was [[retene]] mono substitution products.<ref name=\"Kko: V\"/><ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n\n== Career in the United States ==\nWahlforss travelled to [[Boston]], United States and worked for [[Arthur D. Little]] Inc. simultaneously studying in [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] during 1925\u20131926. in 1926\u20131929 he was the Main Chemist at Industrial Process Ltd and years 1929\u20131933 he worked as Chemist for [[Hammermill Paper Company]] in [[Erie, Pennsylvania]]. In 1933 Wahlforss got a position of Technical Manager in [[Glidden (paints)|Glidden Co.]], where he worked until 1936.<ref name=\"Kko: V\"/><ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n\n== Career in Finland ==\nWahlforss repatriated and got employed as main chemist at [[A. Ahlstr\u00f6m]] Oy [[Varkaus]] factory in 1937. In 1941 he became Executive Director in [[W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]] Selluloosa Oy [[\u00c4\u00e4nekoski]] [[Pulp Mill]] and in the following year he was appointed managing director.<ref name=\"Kko: V\"/> At the time, the Chief Executive of W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4 Group was his older brother Wilhelm Wahlforss. 92% of the \u00c4\u00e4nekoski production was [[newsprint]]. The times were difficult due to the prevailing [[Continuation War|war]] and the company's [[paper machine]] was down most of the time. Later the company built a [[chemical factory]], which produced [[Distilled beverage|spirits]], vinegar, [[yeast]], [[weed control]] agent and [[detergent]]. Eric Wahlforss led the plant until he died in 1951.<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n\n== Positions of trust ==\nWahlforss was the Director of Teknolog-F\u00f6rening in 1920 and Vice Chairman of [[American Chemical Society]] in 1930\u20131933. He was member of the \u00c4\u00e4nekoski [[town council]] in 1941\u20131944.<ref name=\"Kko: V\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nWahlforss was an outdoor person and his main interest was focused on [[hunting]] and dogs.<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n\nDuring his years in the United States, Wahlforss had developed a [[Alcoholism|drinking problem]]. It got worse by time and he started to have difficulties to get along with his assistants and subordinates. He had often disputes with his brother about the way how the company should be managed, but the brothers had cordial relations. In Wilhelm's 60th anniversary celebration, June 1951, Eric gave a speech in which he expressed respect and admire about his brother's achievements. When Eric Wahlforss committed to suicide in the same October, Wilhelm was deeply shocked, and subsequently sold the whole business unit.<ref name=\"Zilliacus: s.168-181\"/>\n\n== Sources ==\n* {{cite book |last=Zilliacus |first=Benedict |author-link=Benedict Zilliacus |year=1984 |title=Wilhelm Wahlforss |language=Finnish |others=Translated from Swedish by Riitta Valaj\u00e4rvi |location=Porvoo |publisher=Oy W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4 Ab |isbn=951-99541-8-X }}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wahlforss, Eric}}\n[[Category:W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]]\n[[Category:Finnish chemists]]\n[[Category:Finnish businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Suicides in Finland]]\n[[Category:1855 births]]\n[[Category:1924 deaths]]