ch towns. An Urban Agglomeration must consist of at least a statutory town and its total population (i.e. all the constituents put together) should not be less than 20,000 as per the 2001 Census. In varying local conditions, there were similar other combinations which have been treated as urban agglomerations satisfying the basic condition of contiguity.\"\n\n===Constituents of Urban Agglomerations ===\nThe constituents of Urban Agglomerations in Odisha, with a population of 1 lakh or above, are noted below:<ref>{{cite web| url = http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/paper2/data_files/India2/Table_4_PR_UAs_1Lakh_and_Above_Appendix.pdf | title = Constituents of urban Agglomerations Having Population 1 Lakh & above |work= Provisional Population Totals, Census of India 2011| publisher = |accessdate = 16 April 2012 }}</ref>\n* Bhubaneswar Urban Agglomeration includes: Bhubaneswar Town (M Corp.), Industrial & Colony Area (OG), Patrapada (OG), Sijua (OG), Ransinghapur (OG), Sarakantara (OG), Bahadalpur (OG), Ebaranga (OG), Raghunathpurjali (OG), Kalarahanga (OG), Injana (OG), Rokat (OG), Kesora (OG), Koradakanta (OG), and Bankual (OG)\n* Cuttack Urban Agglomeration includes:  Cuttack (M Corp.), Choudwar Town (M), and Industrial Area (OG)\n* Rourkela Urban Agglomeration includes: Rourkela Industrial Township (IT), I.D.L.Factory & Other Colony Area (OG), Rourkela Town (M), Kulunga Industrial Estate & Other Colony Area (OG), Jalda Town (CT)\n* Sambalpur Urban Agglomeration includes:  Sambalpur Town (M), Dhankauda & Mathapali Area (OG), Burla Town (NAC), Amsadha Katapali Area (OG), and Hirakud Town (NAC)\n* Baleshwar Urban Agglomeration includes:  Baleshwar Town (M), Baleswwar Industrial Estate (OG), and Remuna Town (NAC)\n* Bhadrak Urban Agglomeration includes:  Bhadrak (M), Randia (OG), Sarmanga (OG), Koranta (OG), Boudhpur (OG), Samaraipur (OG), Erei Town (CT)\n* Baripada Urban Agglomeration includes: Baripada Town (M), Podaastia Business Center Area (OG), Subarnarekha Irrigation Project Colony (OG), and Indupahi (OG)\n\n==Urban Agglomeration constituents==\nUrban Agglomerations constituents with a population above 100,000 as per 2011 census are shown in the table below.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/paper2/data_files/India2/Table_2_PR_Cities_1Lakh_and_Above.pdf | title = Cities having population 1 lakh and above |work= Provisional Population Totals, Census of India 2011 | publisher = |accessdate = 16 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size: 9pt\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"150\" rowspan=\"1\"|Urban Agglomeration\n!width=\"150\" rowspan=\"1\"| Name of Constituent\n!width=\"150\" rowspan=\"1\"| District\n!rowspan=\"1\"|Type*\n!rowspan=\"1\"|Population 2011\n!rowspan=\"1\"|Male\n!rowspan=\"1\"|Female\n!width=\"90\" rowspan=\"1\"|Population<br /> below 5 yrs\n!width=\"90\" rowspan=\"1\"|Literacy Rate\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Bhubaneswar]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Bhubaneswar|Bhubaneswar Town]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Khordha district]]\n|align=\"left\"|M Corp.\n|align=\"right\"|837,737\n|align=\"right\"|445,233\n|align=\"right\"|392,504\n|align=\"right\"|75,237\n|align=\"right\"|93.15\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Cuttack]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Cuttack]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Cuttack district]]\n|align=\"left\"|M Corp.\n|align=\"right\"|606,007\n|align=\"right\"|303,530\n|align=\"right\"|302,477\n|align=\"right\"|48,585\n|align=\"right\"|91.17\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Rourkela]]\n|align=\"left\"| [[Rourkela|Rourkela Industrial Township]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Sundergarh district]]\n|align=\"left\"|IT\n|align=\"right\"|210,412\n|align=\"right\"|109,823\n|align=\"right\"|100,589\n|align=\"right\"|20,399\n|align=\"right\"|86.60\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\n|align=\"left\"| [[Rourkela|Rourkela City]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Sundergarh district]]\n|align=\"left\"|M Corp.\n|align=\"right\"|273,217\n|align=\"right\"|144,949\n|align=\"right\"|128,268\n|align=\"right\"|29,050\n|align=\"right\"|87.95\n|-